headline: Wall Street Expects BlackRock’s Revenue, Assets to Hit Fresh Records
summary: After absorbing big acquisitions, pulling new money into its funds, and riding a rising stock market, analysts expect BlackRock to report new records for both overall assets and third-quarter revenue.  Analysts expect record revenue of $6.27 billion, which would mark a rise of nearly 21% from a year earlier, and record assets under management of $12.46 trillion.  The firm, run by Chief Executive Officer Larry Fink, is the world’s largest money manager.

headline: Banks kick off earnings, Fed Chair Powell speaks: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Tuesday, Oct. 14. Earnings season kicks off, with JPMorgan Chase (JPM), Wells Fargo (WFC), Goldman Sachs (GS), Citi (C), BlackRock (BLK), and Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) all reporting results. Federal Reserve commentary is expected from Fed Chair Jerome Powell, Fed Vice Chair for Supervision Michelle Bowman, Fed Governor Christopher Waller, and Boston Fed President Susan Collins. The Small Business Association's (SBA's) National Federation of Independent Business (NFIB) September Small Business Optimism Index will be published in the morning. Economists are expecting a slight decrease from the prior month. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Review & Preview: A Quick Recovery
summary: Stocks sank on Friday on an apparent escalation of the trade war between Washington and Beijing.  On Monday, they bounced much of the way back after President Donald Trump said over the weekend, “Don’t worry about China.”  The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 588 points, or 1.3%, while the S&P 500 rose 1.6% and the Nasdaq Composite climbed 2.2%.
